Stopwatch Application

Description
This Stopwatch application is a simple Java GUI (Graphical User Interface) program that allows users to start, stop, and reset a stopwatch timer. It displays the elapsed time in hours, minutes, and seconds format.

Features
Start Button: Initiates the stopwatch timer, starting from zero.
Stop Button: Pauses the stopwatch timer, allowing the user to resume later.
Reset Button: Resets the stopwatch timer to zero.
Time Display: Shows the elapsed time in hours, minutes, and seconds format.

How to Use
Run the Main class (Stopwatch) to launch the Stopwatch application.
The stopwatch initially displays "00:00:00".
Click the "START" button to start the stopwatch timer.
Click the "STOP" button to pause the stopwatch timer.
Click the "START" button again to resume timing from where it was paused.
Click the "RESET" button to reset the stopwatch timer back to "00:00:00".
Close the application window to exit.

Contributions
Contributions to enhance the functionality (e.g., adding lap times, improving timer accuracy) or fixing bugs are welcome. Please fork the repository and create a pull request.
